(81, 267, 'Malavya Yoga', 'mala', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Malavya Yoga is one of the Panch Mahapurusha Yoga formed when <a title="shukra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:shukra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shukra</a> is in exaltion or swakshetra position and located in one of the <a title="vishnu sthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a>. In simple terms when Shukra is located in <a title="1st house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">1st house</a>, <a title="4th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=13:matru-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">4th house</a>, <a title="7th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=16:kalatra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">7th house</a> or <a title="10th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=19:karma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">10th house</a> and also the rashi of Shukra happens to be <a title="vrisabha rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=23:taurus&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Vrishabha Rashi</a>, <a title="tula rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=28:libra&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Tula Rashi</a> or <a title="meena rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=33:pisces&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Meena Rashi</a> then Malavya Yoga is formed. Shukra is associated with beauty, wealth, fame and romance. In accordance Malavya Yoga natives beget all the pleasures in life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Malavya Yoga is one yoga where spiritual progress and character of native suffers but inspite of it all, it is a great yoga to have. For people in today''s world are more concerned with worldly pleasures. After all you are guaranteed sufficient wealth, good physique and beauty, abundant fame and blissful romance and marital life along with good children. It wouldn''t be wrong to say 90% of people would want all this in their life. This yoga is not rare as Shukra move every month or so but what is rarity is if Shukra is not afflicted when Malavya Yoga is formed. Generally Shukra, <a title="surya article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Surya</a> and <a title="budh article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=4:budh&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Budh</a> travel together rarely at distance of 2-3 rashis from each other. Surya diminishes the effect of planets like Budh and Shukra when it comes together with them in a rashi. So only checking Shukra in Vishnu Sthana and Uccha or Swakshetra rashi won''t guarantee Malavya Yoga.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Malavya Yoga natives have well developed physique, are strong-minded, wealthy and happy with wife and children. They command good set of vehicles. They are self indulgent, intelligent and if Shukra is in Tula then can be fair in giving justice. They are attractive to others and &nbsp;fond of sexual pleasures. They can even be respected by kings of the country if Malavya Yoga is in good condition.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Downside of all Malavya Yoga is no spiritual progress or character development but upsides far outweigh the downsides.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 14, '2014-03-25 12:16:05', 899, '', '2014-04-16 07:24:34', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:17:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 10, 0, 'malavya yoga, panch mahapurusha yoga, shukra in swakshetra, shukra in uccha rashi, shukra yogas', 'malavya yoga description', 1, 67, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(82, 269, 'Bhadra Yoga', 'bhadra', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bhadra Yoga is formed when <a title="budh article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=4:budh&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Budh</a> occupies the <a title="vishnu sthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a> and is located in Uccha Rashi or Swakshetra. In simpler terms it can only happen in <a title="1st house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">1st house</a>, <a title="4th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=13:matru-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">4th house</a>, <a title="7th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=16:kalatra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">7th house</a> or <a title="10th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=19:karma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">10th house</a> and if Budh is located in <a title="mithuna rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=24:gemini&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Mithuna Rashi</a> or <a title="kanya rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=27:virgo&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Kanya Rashi</a>. Bhadra Yoga is one of yogas which forms the Panch Mahapurusha Yoga (PMY). Compared to other PMY yogas the effects are slightly less as Budh is an impressionable graha and staying close to <a title="surya article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Surya</a> diminishes its effects. If Budh+Surya happens in Kanya Rashi or Mithuna Rashi then along with Bhadra Yoga, an additional Budh-Aditya Yoga is formed which promises intelligence, wealth and fame.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bhadra Yoga natives have well built body and are youthful in looks. Budh is a prince and to some extent these individuals like princely comforts especially if Budh occupies lagna. Budh is the planet which loves to talk articulately and smartely. They are analytical and possess learning of vivid subjects. Though that doesn''t necessarily translate into knowledge. Budh alone in a rashi is quite talkative even though learned it suits better for native to have a planet like <a title="mangal article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Mangal</a> (his enemy), <a title="shani article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shani</a>, <a title="guru article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Guru</a> or Surya with it. They give direction to the articulate and talkative Budh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Natives born with Bhadra Yoga are strong, have well developed face and chest, youthful in appearance and brave like a lion. They are ambitious and progressive. They get on quite well with relatives and are always eager to help relatives. They are progressive and innovative and capable of breakthrough in scientific fields if other grahas are suitable. Progress comes gradually for the native.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Though Bhadra yoga is quite good yoga it is even better if one of the above mentioned grahas combines with Budh in rashi of Budh. That would give better results as compared to Budh alone in own rashi in Vishnu Sthanas. &nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 14, '2014-03-25 12:18:52', 899, '', '2014-04-16 05:46:48', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:19:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 7, 0, 'bhadra yoga, panch mahapurusha yoga, budh aditya yoga, budh yogas, buddh aditya yoga', 'bhadra yoga description', 1, 65, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(83, 271, 'Parivartana Yoga', 'payo', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Parivartana Yoga (PY) is the unique yoga which occurs when two planets exchange each other''s houses. It is called Exchange of Houses in astrology. Ancient Vedic Astrology doesn''t tell much about such yogas and most astrologers tend not to focus on such yogas. Parivartana Yoga is not a Raja Yoga but kind of symbiosis agreement between two concerned grahas which is mutually beneficiary.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;What has largely been observed is this yoga can occur quite frequently in either the Lagna Chart or Navamsha Chart and due care needs to be given before judging whether such yoga would prove fruitful or not.&nbsp;Some of the rules for fruition/cancellation of Parivartana Yoga are described below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1. PY (Parivartana Yoga) &nbsp;can provide beneficial results if it occurs in either Lagna Chart or Navamsha Chart.</p>\r\n<p>2. If two natural benefics (<a title="guru article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Guru</a>, <a title="shukra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:shukra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shukra</a> or <a title="chandra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Chandra</a>) exchange houses then the resultant PY is very good.</p>\r\n<p>3. If two natural malefics (<a title="surya article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Surya</a>, <a title="mangal article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Mangal</a> or <a title="shani article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shani</a>) exchange houses then the resultant PY is decent.</p>\r\n<p>4. If a natural benefic and natural malefic exchange house then the rusult is somewhat good.</p>\r\n<p>5. If there is PY between lords of <a title="vishnu sthana links" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a> then the result is best. It is icing on cake if rule 2 and rule 5 both occur in a horoscope.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6. If there is PY between lord of Vishnu Sthana and <a title="laxmi sthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=85:laxmi&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Laxmi Sthana</a> then results are very good.</p>\r\n<p>7. If there is PY between lord of Vishnu Sthana/Laxmi Sthana and <a title="dushamsthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=89:dushamsthanas&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Dushamsthana</a> then the result is not as desired.</p>\r\n<p>8. If there is a PY between lords of dushamsthanas then result is good but resultant <a title="vpr article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=76:vry&amp;catid=14:imp-yogas&amp;Itemid=165">Vipreeta Raja Yoga</a> gets cancelled.</p>\r\n<p>9. If there is a PY between lords of 1st ,2nd, 4th, 5th, 7th, 9th, 10th, 11th house then results are good but if lord of 3rd house does Parivartana Yoga with any house in horoscope then result are not as desired.</p>\r\n<p>10. PY doesn''t give desired results if the two planets doing Parivartana Yoga are in bad placement in the Navamsha Chart.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Unless there is a Parivartana Yoga between natural benefics, lords of Laxmi Sthanas/Vishnu Sthanas or natural malefics in a dushamsthana the desired results are not observed. There maybe a couple of benefits obtained by the resultant yoga in other locations but native has to work hard to obtain those good results. The very essence of Parivartana Yoga is CHANGE FOR THE BETTER and it can only happen when there is Purushartha applied.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 14, '2014-03-25 12:20:40', 899, '', '2014-04-16 07:19:06', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:21:37', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 8, 0, 'parivartana yoga, exchange of houses, parivartana between two planets, exchange of houses between planets', 'parivartana yoga', 1, 86, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(84, 273, 'Gaja Kesari Yoga', 'gky', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Gaja Kesari Yoga (GKY) is formed when the noble <a title="guru article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Guru</a> occupies <a title="vishnu sthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a> from <a title="chandra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Chandra</a> or Ascendant. Gaj means an elephant in sanskrit while Kesari means a lion. There are different interpretations of the meaning of this yoga but what has been observed is the native with such yoga is influential and formidable but at the same time calm, composed, learned and humble with others. In simpler terms he is courageous like a lion but smart and peaceful like an elephant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Guru in Vishnu Sthanas from Lagna or Chandra is not a big deal. It could happen in a lot of horoscopes. Yet not all of them get the benefits of GKY. What is important is Guru is in kendra in a favorable rashi and not aspected by malefic planets. That happens quit rarely. The best type of GKY is formed when Guru+Chandra are together in Vishnu Sthanas from ascendant and located in <a title="karka rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=25:cancer&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Karka Rashi</a> or <a title="meena rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=33:pisces&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Meena Rashi</a>. Even <a title="dhana rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=30:sagittarius&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Dhana Rashi</a> which belongs to Guru can lessen the effects as it has a fiery nature which doesn''t go well with Chandra who has watery nature. Auspicious placement of Guru+Chandra in a favorable rashi also gives rise to Laxmi Yoga. It is very likely that such natives enjoy full benefits of GKY. GKY doesn''t give expected results if Guru is in <a title="makara rashi article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=31:capricorn&amp;catid=12:12-rashis&amp;Itemid=148">Makara Rashi</a>, aspected by enemy planets or bereft of strength.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Simplest way to find if there is indeed a GKY is to look at the native himself. If he is rich and posseses all comforts from birth and by nature he is calm, good mannered, good cultured and religious then rest assured there is likely to be GKY or some sort of Guru+Chandra associations. This is one of the few yogas which gives results from inception and doesn''t need time to fructify.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 14, '2014-03-25 12:23:25', 899, '', '2014-04-16 06:03:24', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:24:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 7, 0, 'gaja kesari yoga, laxmi yoga, yogas for wealth, guru chandra yoga, guru-chandra yoga', 'gaja kesari yoga description', 1, 74, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(85, 275, 'Laxmi Sthanas', 'laxmi', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Laxmi Sthanas are the trine consisting of <a title="1st house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">1st house</a>, <a title="5th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=14:putra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">5th house</a> and <a title="9th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=18:dharma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">9th house</a>. They are also known as Trikon Sthana (Triangle Houses). Ironically all the 3 concerned houses rule Dharma. Goddess Laxmi is the wife of Lord Vishnu and goddess of wealth and prosperity. She is also the overseer of fortune and luck.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;There is a catch to the name Laxmi Sthanas. 1st house represents character and moral values, 5th house represents knowledge and wisdom and 9th house represents faith and religion. Those who have a good moral values, possess knowledge and wisdom as well as practice faith and religion are said to gain wealth and prosperity. All the 3 houses rule Dharma so in a way, it can be said that wealth and prosperity comes to those who practice Dharma.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;From an astrological perspective Laxmi Sthanas determine fame, fortune and luck. If the house lords of Laxmi Sthanas form <a title="parivartana yoga article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=83:payo&amp;catid=14:imp-yogas&amp;Itemid=165">Parivartana Yoga</a> or located in <a title="vishnu sthanas article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a> then the concerned native is lucky and famous in life. If the house lords of Laxmi Sthanas are in <a title="dushamsthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=89:dushamsthanas&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">dushamsthanas</a> or debilitated then native maybe bereft of fame and fortune.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 19, '2014-03-25 12:28:14', 899, '', '2014-04-16 11:14:11', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:29:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 7, 0, 'vedic astrology, laxmi sthanas, trikona sthanas, dharma sthanas, dharma houses', 'laxmi sthana in astrology', 1, 99, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(86, 277, 'Vishnu Sthanas', 'vishnu', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Vishnu Sthanas also known as Kendra Sthanas are the quadrant of <a title="1st house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">1st house</a>, <a title="4th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=13:matru-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">4th house</a>, <a title="7th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=16:kalatra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">7th house</a> and <a title="10th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=19:karma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">10th house</a> respectively. Each of them rules an important aspect of life''s goal. 1st house provides Dharma, 10th house provides Artha, 7th house provides Kama while 4th house provides Moksha.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;There is a reason why this houses are named as Vishnu Sthanas. Lord Vishnu is called the Palanhaar or Provider. He is charged with the duty of providing basic amenities of life to the people to survive. In similar manner the 4 houses of Vishnu Sthanas are charged with providing the basic amenities of life for survival. 1st house provides health and character, 4th house provides education, nurturing and shelter, 7th house provides progeny and partner to reach higher conscious and 10th house provides fame, popularity and social standing.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; In vedic astrology if there is strength in Vishnu Sthanas it is observed that all the evils in <a title="dushamsthana article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=89:dushamsthanas&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Dushamsthanas</a> or other house can produce no harm to the native. If none of the 4 houses in Vishnu Sthana have strength then native cannot make anything out of himself no matter how hard he tries. Most of the auspicious yoga involve Vishnu Sthanas in one way or other.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 19, '2014-03-25 12:32:14', 899, '', '2014-07-21 10:46:57', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:33:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 6, 0, 'vishnu sthanas, kendra houses, vedic astrology, astrology tutorials', 'vishnu sthanas in astrology', 1, 89, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(87, 279, 'Prarabdha', 'prarabdha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Vedic Astrology there are concepts of Prarabdha and Purushartha. Prarabdha in English means Fate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Prarabdha of an individual plays a big part in shaping his life. If an individual is meant to rise from Rags to Riches then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. If he is meant to fall down from a top position in life then Prarabdha pushes him in that direction. It all depends on karma of an individual or in other words Purushartha. To a believer of Prarabdha, fate controls the destiny while for a believer of Purushartha, hard work controls the destiny. Actually the reality is somewhere in the middle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Prarabdha and Purushartha are not on collision course but rather run parallel and meet at some point of the road. The Purushartha of today becomes the Prarabdha of tomorrow. The Prarabdha faced today maybe a result of Purshartha of yesterday. Similarly today''s Prarabdha may decide the Purushartha for tomorrow. In astrological terms the placement and aspect of benefic planets like <a title="guru article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Guru</a>, <a title="shukra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:shukra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shukra</a> and <a title="chandra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Chandra</a> drive the good Prarabdha while placement and aspect of malefic planets like <a title="shani article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shani</a>, <a title="mangal article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Mangal</a>, <a title="rahu article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=8:rahu&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Rahu</a> and <a title="ketu article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=9:ketu&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Ketu</a> suggest bad Prarabdha which befalls a native. But there is the quintessential question as to where should one apply Prarabdha and where should one apply Purushartha. Vedic Astrology and ancient Astrology Text suggests leaving matters of Artha Houses (<a title="2nd house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=11:dhana-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">2nd house</a>, <a title="6th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=15:rog-sthana&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">6th house</a> and <a title="10th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=19:karma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">10th house</a>) and Kama Houses (<a title="3rd house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=12:bandhu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">3rd house</a>, <a title="7th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=16:kalatra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">7th house</a> and <a title="11th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=20:labh-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">11th house</a>) to Prarabdha. Well to be more accurate leave matters of Savings, Popularity in Media, Matters of Debt, Marriage, Business Partnership (success or failure in partnership), Career Standing, Financial Gains and Quality and Quantity of Friends to Prarabdha. Not every matter in the concerned houses is better to leave to Prarabdha but knowing that Artha Houses and Kama Houses are driven by Prarabdha saves pain in future as they are beyond one''s control.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;As Kabir rightly said in his doha:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Manushya kadi balwaan nahi; Samaya sab se balwaan<br />Kaabe Arjuna lutiyo; Wahi dhanush wahi baan</h4>\r\n<p>Translation: Time is far more powerful compared to the human. The greatest of the warrior Arjuna lost to a bunch of tribesman of forest even though he was using the same quiver and arrows which he used to defeat mighty warriors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Countless stories exist to justify Saint Kabir''s views. But the point put across is not to get arrogant or conceited if you find victory and not to get deflated and lose hope at loss. Accept your Prarabdha and work towards your Purushartha.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 19, '2014-03-25 12:35:27', 899, '', '2014-04-16 11:25:47', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:35:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 6, 0, 'vedic astrology, fate in astrology, prarabdha in astrology, learn vedic astrology, vedic astrology tutorials', 'prarabdha in astrology', 1, 83, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(88, 281, 'Purushartha', 'purushartha', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Vedic Astrology the term Purushartha means Karma or doing your duty (not just any work). It is the driving force and the foremost reason why astrology gets it wrong in terms of forecasting future of the native. Just like there are Variants, Pie Values, Friction and Worst Case Scenarios in Mathematics, Science and Programming which cause calculations to go awry there is Purushartha in astrology which puts all the calculations as meaningless and native achieves things which cannot be calculated at birth. This single word maligns astrology like no other one does yet this article is only meant to praise this nemesis called Purushartha cause it is truly a great nemesis.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purushartha is nothing but hard work without any sort of expectations in return. The very essence of Bhagvad Gita can summarize Purushartha like no one else can:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;"One cannot achieve anything without doing Karma (Purushartha). Don''t try to get anything for free. No work is bereft of gains. One should not ever get depressed in life. One should not lose confidence while doing his Karma (Purushartha)." -- Pandurang Athvale</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Purushartha and <a title="prarabdha article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=87:prarabdha&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Prarabdha</a> are not on collision course but run parellel and intersect at some point of the long road. So people who loathe fate and luck should not get agitated at those who believe in it and those who believe in fate and luck should understand that today''s hard work is tomorrow''s good luck. Some people are born with the knowledge of what Purushartha he needs to pursue to be successful in life. Generally they are the people who taunt everyone else with early success. What they fail to realize is that Prarabdha was responsible for making them pursue the respected field and gain success. By taunting others today''s bad karma would become bad Prarabdha for tomorrow and hit them hard on the face.&nbsp;In similar manner people who believe too much in luck and fate refuse to get out of their cocoon and work hard towards a fixed objective. What they fail to realize is today''s Purushartha would result in good karma and ultimately good Prarabdha in the future.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;There is a dilemma in people when it comes to using Purushartha or &nbsp;applying Prarabdha. Vedic Astrology and Ancient Astrological Texts suggest trying hard (Purushartha) for matters of Dharma Houses (<a title="1st house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10:tanu-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">1st house</a>, <a title="5th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=14:putra-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">5th house</a> and <a title="9th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=18:dharma-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">9th house</a>) as well as Moksha Houses (<a title="4th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=13:matru-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">4th house</a>, <a title="8th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=17:mrityu-sthana&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">8th house</a> and <a title="12th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=21:vyaya-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">12th house</a>). To be more precise one should try hard for a good character, good health, good education, being religious as well try hard to get peace and happiness, think of death and rebirths and also work towards minimizing losses as well as gaining liberation from cycle of life and death by attaining Moksha.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Astrologers are generally not sought until situation is worse and all hope is lost. Some people are highly negative and consult astrologers to find out the right time to eat and sleep. What I personally advise is to learn about your Purushartha or goal of your life from astrologers as nothing is wrong in that. After that only visit him in times of calamity for solutions if possible through astrology. An honest astrologer is sure to give you right advise about the right course of action to take.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Finally don''t lose hope when all is lost and don''t get over the moon when you gain everything you''ve set out to do. Both are temperory. Your actions are permanent. So stick to your Purushartha and learn to enjoy the Prarabdha which has befallen you whether it is good or bad.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 19, '2014-03-25 12:38:56', 899, '', '2014-07-21 10:47:13', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-25 11:39:45', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 8, 0, 'purushartha, hard work in astrology, learn vedic astrology, vedic astrology tutorials', 'purushartha in vedic astrology', 1, 80, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(89, 287, 'Dushamsthanas', 'dushamsthanas', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Dushamsthanas is a term used to describe the 6th house, 8th house and 12th house in Vedic Astrology. The word&nbsp;<strong>''du''&nbsp;</strong>means bad in sanskrit. <a title="6th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=15:rog-sthana&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">6th house</a>, <a title="8th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=17:mrityu-sthana&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">8th house</a> and <a title="12th house article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=21:vyaya-bhava&amp;catid=11:12-bhavas&amp;Itemid=119">12th house</a> are not necessarily bad houses so to speak but the matters governed by them are considered bad by humans. 6th house governs sickness, debts and addictions. 8th house govers death and suffering while 12th house governs prisons and monetary losses.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Naturally not many people find this subjects fascinating. But knowing is believing and believing leads to change. Till there is sickness there is no value for health, till there is death there is no value for life and till there is loss there is no value of careful spending. It is an irony in itself that Dushamsthanas are not studied or asked about until there is death, disease, sickness and monetary losses. The more subtle and good matters of <a title="laxmi sthanas article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=85:laxmi&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Laxmi Sthanas</a> and <a title="vishnu sthanas article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86:vishnu&amp;catid=19:main-articles&amp;Itemid=117">Vishnu Sthanas</a> are carefully deciphered using astrology. Everyone who goes to an astrologer is more interested in knowing his timing of marriage, his education, the money he may earn and the comforts he would enjoy. Alas!! These things are in the hands of Prarabdha. But the matters of dushamsthans specifically addiction, debt, sickness and loss as well as suffering are in our hands. We may not be able to prevent sickness but we can definitely work towards cure. We cannot prevent monetary losses but we can very well plan to cut short these losses. We cannot plan for suffering we are receiving but we can very well plan to ease those suffering.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;It is quite amusing to know no one gives a damn about Dushamsthans until tragedy strikes. If you are a student of astrology then it would be a great idea to give a balanced view and a balanced view cannot be given until studying the dushamsthans. Astrology Text says the malefic planets (<a title="shani article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=7:shani&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shani</a>, <a title="rahu article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=8:rahu&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Rahu</a>, <a title="surya article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=1:surya&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Surya</a>, <a title="ketu article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=9:ketu&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Ketu</a> &amp; <a title="mangal article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=3:mangal&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Mangal</a>) are good in Dushamsthans while the benefic planets (<a title="guru article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:guru&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Guru</a>, <a title="chandra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=2:chandra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Chandra</a> and <a title="shukra article link" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:shukra&amp;catid=10:9-planets&amp;Itemid=118">Shukra</a>) are bad. But the rashi, planetary lord, navamsha position and various astrological yogas also need to observed before giving a final verdict.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In case of dushamsthans it is best to check for tenant or co-tenants of dushamsthanas and their relationship with the dushamsthana lord via aspect or joining. Then check the drishtis of various planets on the dushamsthan house. Finally check if dushamsthana lord is in good disposition. If these three points indicate a positive outlook then nothing bad can fall on native with matters of the dushamsthana house. It is rarely possible that whole of native remains good or bad but if dushamsthana houses are having negative placements then rest assured whole life would have difficulties, diseases, debt and despair. It is imperative to get the dushamsthana houses checked first before moving towards matters of Vishnu Sthanas and Laxmi Sthanas.&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 19, '2014-04-05 09:23:10', 899, '', '2014-04-16 11:41:07', 899, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-04-08 06:29:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 11, 0, 'dushamsthans, 6th house, 8th house, 12th house, debt astrology, health astrology, sickness astrology', 'dushamsthanas in astrology', 1, 90, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '');
