(2, 'com_content.article', 'Kaal Sarp Yoga- The Great Hoax', 'kaal-sarp', '<p><img class="pull-left" title="rahu-ketu " src="images/Rahu-ketu.png" alt="Rahu-Ketu Trajectory" width="440" height="256" /></p>\r\n<p>                </p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><strong>Rahu &amp; Ketu are north and south nodes</strong></p>\r\n<p>  Kaal Sarp Yoga is indeed a great misconception introduced in astrology. Most of the ancient literature on astrology never mentioned about Kaal Sarpyoga. Of course as a subject evolves and there is research done and a fewnew concepts are bound to rise up but certainly concepts like Kaal Sarp Yogaare hard to fathom. When you notice this yoga in your horoscope or get notified by an astrologer be sure to understand the surreal fear inserted into this yoga.When a person doesn''t get the desired success in life and he goes to an astrologer the astrologer probably checks for conditions like Vish Yoga, Kaal Sarpa Yoga, Planets in Dushamsthanas or Neecha Grahas in horoscope. If even one of them is present theastrologeris sure to make a moolah out of it.</p>\r\n<p>  To be accurateRahu and Ketu are not planets according to Astronomyand even Astrology mentions them as Chayya Grahas or Shadow Planets. But since ancient texts do point to a demon called Rahu whose head got severed by Lord Vishnu we would do injustice to Rahu and Ketu if we do not considerthem in Vedic Astrology. Having said that Kaal Sarp Yoga is hard to imagine to be true. Why?Cause two imaginary planets cannot hold your whole life to a ransom. I''ve come across quite a few people in life with Kaal Sarpa Yoga and most of them are to a point unsuccessful in life despite best efforts. But I''ve yet to come across any of Kaal Sarp Yoga natives whose condition is as adverse as people withShrapit Yoga (Rahu-Shani in same sign) or Vish Yoga (Shani-Chandra in one sign) or benefics in Dushamsthanas.There are enough success stories associated with Kaal Sarpa Yogas like Jawaharlal Nehru, Margaret Thatcher, Paul Mccartney and Alfred Hitchcock among others to dispel the illusion of Kaal Sarpa Yoga.</p>\r\n<p>  One of the most important thing to note is Kaal Sarpa Yoga has all planets on one side of horoscope if Rahu is counted as lagna and Ketu as 7th house. What that means is there are less chances of aspects as most grahas cast a drishti on 7th house from themselves. There is a far greater chance of planets improving with time as long as there is no aspect involved. Long story short Kaal Sarp Yoga gives the best chance to improving a grahas condition in rashi as long as Shanior Rahu doesn''t aspect that house and if Rahu is not a co-tenant. If you look at the other articles on Kaal Sarpa Yoga they are sure to give you indications that conditions improve after certain time for Kaal Sarp Yoga natives. What they don''t tell you is conditions improve not due to Kaal Sarp Yoga but cause grahas mature and learn the art of co-existence if placed in same rashi, that grahas learn to turn adversity into opportunity and weakness into strengths with time. If Shani/Rahu''s aspect is present or Rahu as co-tenant is present then it is impossible for grahas to improve with time and the whole fault goes into the imaginary Kaal Sarp Yoga.</p>\r\n<p>  Those who are student of astrology should try looking at various horoscopes with or without Kaal Sarpa Yoga. If there is Rahu in co-existence with a particular graha or many grahas then none of them improve with time. In similar manner those with aspects by Shani and Rahu also don''t improve much with time. But those planets without aspect of Shani/Rahu and Rahu as co-tenant are sure to improve over time irrelevant of Kaap Sarp Yoga or any other yoga present in horoscope. If you have any queries regarding this article feel free to ask in comments section.</p>\r\n<p>  </p>\r\n<p></p>', -2, '', 0, 1, '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 140, '', '2014-07-20 07:55:05', 140, '2014-07-21 07:34:16', '*', '2014-07-20 12:45:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 91, 73, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 17, 24, 0, 'kaal sarp yoga, rahu, ketu', 'kaal sarp yoga description', 14, '', 1);
